  "text": "Plasmid analysis. Plasmid DNA was isolated by the method of Kado and Liu (6) and analyzed by agarose gel electrophoresis with E. coli 39R861 as a plasmid molecular mass marker [CITATION_1] . Plasmid sizes were determined with reference to 39R861 and the 38-MDa S. enteritidis serovar-specific plasmid (SSP). Plasmid DNA was transferred to Hybond N hybridization membranes (Amersham International, Amersham, United Kingdom) by capillary blotting. The presence of the Salmonella plasmid virulence (spv) region was determined by hybridization to a digoxigenin-labelled probe comprising a 437-bp fragment encoding the spvC virulence gene, prepared by PCR with oligonucleotide primers (Boehringer Mannheim, Lewes, United Kingdom) (4a). Detection of the hybridization signal was done according to the manufacturer's recommendations.",
